title: Old World Meats Recalls Roast Beef Products Due to Misbranding and Undeclared Allergen
summary: WASHINGTON, May 22, 2015 Old World Meats, a Duluth, Minn. establishment, is recalling approximately 12 pounds of roast beef products due to misbranding and undeclared allergens, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
